- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a novel reranking model for transition-based parsing, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses bidirectional LSTM and dropout to improve the parsing accuracy. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents a new approach to parsing that involves searching for the best dependency tree using a global scorer. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to improve the parsing accuracy. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses bidirectional LSTM, which is a common technique in computer vision.
